          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Coretta Scott King Mid-Decade Redistricting Prohibition Act of 2015</strong></p> <p> Prohibits any state whose congressional districts have been redistricted after a decennial census from carrying out another redistricting until after the next apportionment of Representatives following a decennial census, unless a court requires such state to conduct a subsequent redistricting to comply with the Constitution or enforce the Voting Rights Act of 1965. </p> <p>Makes this Act applicable to any congressional redistricting which occurs after the regular decennial census conducted during 2020. </p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
